{"key":"processedPost-10941975","value":{"id":10941975,"first":10937819,"last":10958143,"when":1251318318,"utime":"08/26/09 11:25 PM","content":"The fan doesn't need to be running in a closet with the terrarium.&nbsp; You might put the fan on a timer, but it's forcing air through the holes in the sides, drying out the air.&nbsp; You want the air to enter the bottom below the perlite, and then absorb moisture as it travels up.&nbsp;  If you're going to run the fan, you'll have to mist a lot more.<br />You can mist the cakes directly.&nbsp; You can also pour water directly on the pile of verm on top if needed.&nbsp; Just don't let your cakes get waterlogged.<br />RR","title":"Re: Misting Cakes Directly"}}